name: Crime_Data_from_2020_to_2023_in_LA
information: The dataset 'Crime Data from 2020 to 2023 in LA.csv' is a log of crime reports in Los Angeles spanning a period from January 1st, 2020 to December 31st, 2023. Each row in the dataset represents a unique crime event, detailing when it was reported (Date Rptd) and actually occurred (Date Occ), the time of occurrence (Time Occ), where it happened (Area Name), the type of crime (Crm Type), information about the victim such as age (Vict Age) and sex (Vict Sex), the current status of the case (Status Desc), and precise location coordinates (LAT for latitude and LON for longitude). There are 21 distinct areas where crimes have been logged, 43 different crime types recorded, and a range of victim ages and sexes captured. Location coordinates are given as numbers with latitude ranging up to 34.3343 and longitude down to -118.6676.

name: Titanic dataset
information: The Titanic dataset provides information on the passengers of the ill-fated RMS Titanic, covering their demographics, ticket details, and survival status. Each row represents a unique passenger with fields detailing their personal characteristics, ticket information, and travel accommodations. The dataset is pivotal in studying survival patterns, understanding the impact of personal and socio-economic factors, and training machine learning models for predictive tasks in survival analysis.

name: Salary Data
information: The dataset 'Salary Data.csv' provides information on the salaries of individuals along with their demographics, job title, and experience. Each row represents an individual's data including age, gender, education level, job title, years of experience, and current salary. This dataset can be useful for analyzing salary trends based on demographic factors, job roles, and professional experience.

name: Impact_of_Remote_Work_on_Mental_Health
information: The dataset examines the effects of remote work on employees' mental health, covering demographics, work conditions, and wellbeing factors. It contains records for 5000 employees, each detailing personal and professional data, work environment, mental health status, and satisfaction levels. This information offers insights into how remote work influences aspects like work-life balance, stress, and company support.

name: Walmart_Sales
information: The dataset captures sales data for Walmart stores, providing insights into how various factors affect weekly sales across different locations. Each row represents the weekly sales data for a specific store on a specific date, along with contextual factors such as temperature, fuel price, CPI, and unemployment rate. The dataset enables analysis of sales patterns, seasonality, and economic influences, offering valuable information for business and economic research.

name: Cardiovascular Disease dataset
information: The dataset 'Cardiovascular Disease dataset.csv' contains medical information for 70,000 individuals, each represented by a row. Each entry includes personal and clinical data such as age, gender, height, weight, blood pressure, cholesterol and glucose levels, and lifestyle factors. It aims to predict or analyze the presence of cardiovascular disease using these attributes.
